<TITLE> Six jailed for Bhola by-polls offences </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 3 (bdnews24.com)  Six people have been sentenced to two years in jail for trying to cast false votes and create troubles in Apr 24 by-polls for Bhola-3 constituency. Election commissioner M Sakhawat Hussain told the reporters on Monday that the convicts were in prison now. He said they have also been fined Tk 500 each and will suffer a further one month in jail failing to pay it.. The commissioner said Bhola chief judicial magistrate Kiran Shankar Halder sent the list of convicts and description of the trial to the Election Commission. He said the convicts' offences, in the polling centres of Tajmuddin and Lalmohan upazilas, were condemnable for two-year to seven-year imprisonment under the Representation of People Order 1972. The convicts are Mohammed Hakim Ali of Tajmuddin upazila, Shakil Mahmud Parag, Humayun Kabir, M Abu Taher and Abdur Rahman of Lalmohan, and M Sanaullah of Comilla district. Hakim Ali was sentenced by senior judicial magistrate M Masum Billah and the others by senior judicial magistrates Muhammad Zakaria and M Shibli Noman Khan. The commissioner said they had taken adequate measures to hold the Bhola by-poll in a free and fair manner. Awami League candidate Nurunnabi Chowdhury Shaon defeated BNP's Hafizuudin Ahmed in the poll. Sakhawat said measures will be stricter in future elections, including the local government ones. He sought cooperation from all including the political parties. bdne
